commText: Ravindra and Gaikwad are at the crease. Ravindra is on strike. Abhishek Sharma will open the attack
Abhishek Sharma to Ravindra, 1 run, flatter and just outside off, whipped off the back-foot to long-on for a single
Abhishek Sharma to Gaikwad, 1 run, tossed up on middle, Gaikwad shimmies around and then nudges with soft hands towards mid-wicket for a single

Abhishek Sharma to Ravindra, FOUR, nicely played, tossed up and sliding down leg - Ravindra bends down low, rolled his wrists and then swept it backward of square on the on-side, first boundary of the night
Abhishek Sharma to Ravindra, no run, flighted delivery on off, Ravindra backs away and chops it back at the bowler
Abhishek Sharma to Ravindra, 1 run, pushed through by Abhishek, worked down to long-on for a single
Abhishek Sharma to Gaikwad, no run, tossed up on the leg-stump line as Gaikwad backed away, blocked back at the bowler
Bhuvneshwar to share the new ball, a slip in place
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Ravindra, no run, short of a good length and at the hips, tucked off the back-foot to mid-wicket
Bhuvneshwar to Ravindra, 1 run, on a good length and around the off-stump channel, pushed to the left of mid-off for a quick single

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, FOUR, beautifully played, on a good length and just outside off - Gaikwad shuffled across, played with an open face and then merely pushed it onto the off-side, bounced over backward point's head and rolls away to the ropes - that's some sublime timing
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, length ball at the stumps, Gaikwad leans across and defends it to the on-side
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, excellent comeback from Bhuvneshwar - pitched up in that channel just outside off, angles in and then nips away slightly, beating Gaikwad's forward prod
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, steered with a closed face to third man
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 2 runs, fuller length delivery on the pads, clipped away over square leg - Gaikwad calls for the second and rushes back with ease
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, no run, back of a length and angling across the right-hander, dabbed straight to the fielder at backward point
T Natarajan to Gaikwad, 1 run, on a good length and in that channel wide of off, stabbed square on the off-side for a single
T Natarajan to Ravindra, FOUR, hammered, on a length and angling back into the left-hander - Ravindra picks the length early and then shovels it over mid-wicket, bounces away to the ropes in a hurry

T Natarajan to Ravindra, 1 run, a direct hit and Ravindra had given up - Markram had more time then he thought, was driven straight to him and Ravindra set-off for a suicidal single - he had all the three stumps to aim and missed

T Natarajan to Gaikwad, FOUR, classy, back of a length and well wide of off - Gaikwad waits on it, plays with an open face and then slices the cut square past point, beats the fielder in the deep for a boundary
Bhuvneshwar to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bhuvneshwar to Ravindra, out Caught by Markram!! Markram makes amends and Bhuvneshwar has his 1st wicket of IPL 2024 - was a back of a length delivery that was angled across the left-hander, was too wide to play, but Ravindra backed himself on the pull, gets a massive top-edge, high and down mid-on's throat. Markram has plenty of time to settle under the skier as he moved to his right and pouched with glee. Ravindra c Markram b Bhuvneshwar 12(9) [4s-2]
Ajinkya Rahane, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, fuller length delivery on off, defended back at the bowler

Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, no run, Bhuvneshwar has an excellent match-up against Rahane and he nearly gets him for the 7th time, on a good length and straightening from the angle, Rahane was early into the tuck, closed the face of the bat and the leading edge popped back over the bowler's head
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, Rahane drives and gets a thick edge to third man for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, Bhuvneshwar shortens the length and gets it to hold its line outside off, draws a meek poke and Gaikwad is lucky to haven't edged it
Ajinkya Rahane vs Bhuvneshwar Kumar in the IPL (before today) Runs: 90 Balls: 103 Dismissals: 6 Avg: 15 SR: 87.37 4s/6s: 14/0 Dots: 60
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven firmly and straight to the fielder at mid-off
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Rahane, no run, on a good length and just outside off, stabbed to the left of mid-off and Rahane wanted a single, sent back and he beats Abhisheks' shy at the striker's end
Cummins to Rahane, SIX, clubbed, length ball on off - he spots the length early and then swings through the line, sends it soaring - high and deep into the stands at long-on
Cummins to Rahane, no run, Cummins drags the length back around off, dabbed with an open face to backward point
Cummins to Rahane, no run, on a good length and just outside off - eased with an open face to backward point
Cummins to Rahane, 1 run, the slower short ball from Cummins - Rahane drags the pull behind square on the on-side for a single
Cummins to Gaikwad, no run, on a length and around the off-stump channel, defended to the off-side
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, FOUR, thumped, length ball on off, Rahane leans forward, high elbow and a straight as he punches it back over the non-striker's head, couple of bounces and over the ropes
Bhuvneshwar to Rahane, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, dabbed in front of backward point for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, creamed straight to the fielder at extra-cover

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, FOUR, nicely played, back of a length and well wide of off - Gaikwad opens the face of the bat and then reaches out on the steer, wa sin the air and well wide of the fielder at third man, who was inside the ring
Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, no run, Bhuvneshwar shortens the length outside off, defended with an open face to backward point

Bhuvneshwar to Gaikwad, SIX, lovely, pitched up by Bhuvneshwar - Gaikwad leans forward, presents a straight bat, high elbow and a lofted drive back over the bowler's head, soared all the way and bounced in front of the sight-screen - 15 off the over

Powerplay summary: -- Ball is holding in the pitch sometimes -- CSK start slow, then raise tempo -- Bhuvi keeps it tight in the channel -- Rachin dismissed for 12 by Bhuvi (3.1) -- Rahane plays couple of delightful shots -- Gaikwad finishes powerplay in style
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Markande to Rahane, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, pushed in front of long-on for a single
Markande to Gaikwad, 1 run, Gaikwad shimmies down the pitch to a well flighted delivery and punches it to long-off for a single
Markande to Rahane, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked past square leg for a single
Markande to Gaikwad, 1 run, pushed through by Markande, Gaikwad goes back and tucks it to long-on for a single
Markande to Rahane, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, eased square on the off-side for a single
Markande to Gaikwad, 1 run, flatter and at the stumps, whipped down to long-on for a single
Shahbaz Ahmed, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Shahbaz Ahmed to Gaikwad, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Catching practice at long-on - A tame dismissal for Gaikwad, was tossed up on middle and Gaikwad backed himself to clear the fielder at long-on, but he got slightly too close to the ball and ended up dragging it off the inner half, straight down Samad's throat, at long-on. Gaikwad squirms in disappointment, got a start and then threw it away. Gaikwad c Abdul Samad b Shahbaz Ahmed 26(21) [4s-3 6s-1]
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shivam Dube, no run, pushed through quicker and just outside off, stabbed to the right of cover - they think about a run and then decide against it
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shivam Dube, no run, dragged short and wide of off, Dube was shaping for the cut and missed
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shivam Dube, SIX, smashed, sheer power from Dube - tad too full and wide of off, he reaches out and then hammers the drive, high and over long-on for a maximum
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shivam Dube, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Dube - Shahbaz goes full and wide of off, Dube reaches out and then hammers the drive over cover, one bounce and over the ropes
Gaikwad vs Shahbaz in the IPL Runs: 2 Balls: 5 Dismissals: 2
Shahbaz Ahmed to Shivam Dube, 1 run, pushed through outside off, hacked down to long-on for a single
Markande to Shivam Dube, FOUR, cracking shot, the wrong 'un from Markande, but the length is short and it's wide as well, cut away square past point for a boundary
Markande to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, tossed up on off, nudged in front of square on the on-side and Dube rushes across for a second
Markande to Shivam Dube, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Markande to Rahane, 1 run, tossed up on middle, nudged down to long-on for a single
Shivam Dube pulls out at the last moment and Markande breaks the stumps, but it doesn't count

Markande to Shivam Dube, SIX, Dube is loving this - flighted delivery outside leg, he gets down low and then sweeps it fiercely, Natarajan at deep square leg thought he had a chance, but he simply watches it sail over his head and into the crowd
Markande to Shivam Dube, 1 run, the wrong 'un from Markande, cut away in front of square on the off-side for a single, 15 off the over

Time for the strategic break. Brian Lara said this is a batting beauty and on that account SRH will not be too unhappy with the score, but Dube is in and he's looking dangerous. They've bowled a couple of overs of spin at him and it hasn't worked, will Cummins go back to pace?
Cummins is back and he's starting from round the wicket
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Shivam Dube, no run, on a good length and tucking Dube for room, pushed back at the bowler
Cummins to Shivam Dube, no run, fuller length delivery and angling into the left-hander, nudged to the on-side
Cummins to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, short of a good length and well wide of off, Dube backs away and then slices the drive over backward point, comes back for the second
Change of bat for Dube
Cummins to Shivam Dube, 1 run, the slower bouncer, bowled into the pitch and it's stabbed square past point for a single
Cummins to Rahane, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, steered uppishly and behind square on the off-side - Unadkat scampers across, puts in the dive and saves three runs for his team

Cummins to Shivam Dube, no run, that's another excellent save, preventing a certain boundary - length delivery outside off and Dube hammered the drive, to the left of the fielder who dived and made an acrobatic stop
Jaydev Unadkat, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Unadkat to Rahane, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, Unadkat, from round the wicket - Rahane is cramped for room on the pull and finds mid-wicket

Unadkat to Rahane, 2 runs, tad fuller and just outside off, looked like the cutter and Rahane was undone by the length, scoops it in the air and gets enough to clear backward point, back for the second
Unadkat to Rahane, wide, the slower bouncer from Unadkat, but it sails over Rahane's head and is called as a wide
Unadkat to Rahane, no run, short of a good length and angling into the right-hander, beat Rahane's pull for pace and rolls to the off-side, off hius thigh-pad

Unadkat to Rahane, leg byes, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, not much pace and Rahane jams an inside edge onto his thigh-pad, rolls to the off-side for a single. Given as a leg-bye though
Unadkat to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, driven down to long-off for a single
Unadkat to Rahane, 1 run, the slower short ball from Unadkat, Rahane backs away and pulls it past square leg for a single
Natarajan, from round the wicket
T Natarajan [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Rahane, 1 run, top-edge and safe, banged in short and into the surface, rushes Rahane for pace on the pull, a big top-edge and he's lucky that the ball landed well in front of long leg
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, hammered, a friendly short ball from Natarajan - Dube clears his front leg and then pummels the pull over mid-wicket, sent it sailing into the stands
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, SIX, back-to-back sixes for Dube - Natarajan goes full, but this is right in Dube's arc - he gets his front leg out of the way and then shovels it over deep mid-wicket
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, no run, the slower short ball from Natarajan - dabbed straight to the fielder at backward point
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, much better from Natarajan, yorker length delivery outside off and it's squeezed past cover for a couple, brings up the 50-run stand
T Natarajan to Shivam Dube, no run, another perfect yorker from Natarajan, Dube jams his bat down and squeezes it to mid-off, 15 off the over

Unadkat to Rahane, 2 runs, another mishit and Rahane gets away once again - came off the bottom of the bat as he looked to hoick one over mid-wicket, the ball dropping well wide of the fielder in the deep
Unadkat to Rahane, no run, Unadkat shortens the length and bowls one into the surface, pushed off the back-foot to mid-off

Unadkat to Rahane, FOUR, just wide of Cummins at mid-off, he leapt across, went with his right-hand, but the ball was wide of his reach - slower ball from Unadkat, Rahane backed away and muscled it back past the bowler
Unadkat to Rahane, 1 run, another slower ball from Unadkat, chipped down to long-on for a single
Unadkat to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, no pace to work with and Dube mistimes the hack to mid-off
Unadkat to Rahane, 2 runs, on a good length and just outside off, driven with an open face and behind square on the off-side, Rahane comes back for the second
They've taken the strategic break. Shivam Dube is on the move, but change of pace is working for SRH. Can they keep CSK down to 180 or less?
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Shivam Dube, 1 run, right in the blockhole on off, Shivam Dube jams it out towards long-on
Cummins to Rahane, 2 runs, back of a length ball angling in on off, Rahane works it nicely to the right of deep square leg and rushes back for the second run
Cummins to Rahane, 1 run, a skiddy length ball on off, Rahane hacks it to the fielder at deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Bhuvneshwar!! Cummins gets the dangerous Shivam Dube and he is cock-a-hoop! This is his 50th IPL wicket. He switches back to round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls a slower bouncer well outside off. Shivam Dube has to reach out to it and he is not sure what to do with it. Ends up guiding it tamely straight to Bhuvi at backward point and he accepts it gleefully. Shivam Dube c Bhuvneshwar b Cummins 45(24) [4s-2 6s-4]
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Jadeja, no run, low full-toss around off, Jadeja leans ahead and eases it towards backward point
Cummins to Jadeja, 1 run, 121.1kph slower short ball outside off, Jadeja waits for it and pulls it to deep mid-wicket to get off the mark

Highlights (Overs 7-14) -- 72/2 -- Gaikwad dismissed by Shahbaz for 26 (7.1) -- Dube hits spinners out of the attack -- CSK given a boost by Dube's powerhitting -- Rahane struggling to raise tempo -- Unadkat, Cummins using the cutters well -- Cummins removes Dube for 45 (13.4)
Unadkat to Jadeja, 1 run, 126.2kph back of a length ball angling in, Jadeja punches it towards mid-off for a brisk single. That one held up a bit on the pitch
Unadkat to Rahane, 1 run, Unadkat switches to round the wicket and bowls a 108.7kph length ball on off, Rahane hits it down to long-on

Unadkat to Jadeja, FOUR, back to over the wicket to the left-hander. A slower shortish delivery outside off at 111 clicks, Jadeja uses his feet and has to reach out to it. He plays a forehand smash wide of extra cover and gets the desired result
Unadkat to Jadeja, no run, 128.3kph full ball outside off, Jadeja drags his heave straight to mid-wicket
Crowd Watch: 35667 in attendance today
Unadkat to Jadeja, 1 run, 108.3kph slower short ball cutting in from outside off, pulled to deep square leg
Unadkat to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Unadkat to Rahane, out Caught by Markande!! The slower balls are doing the trick for SRH! 104.8kph off-pace ball wide outside off, Rahane reaches out to it and throws his bat at it but only manages to slice it towards backward point. Markande leaps to his left and takes a smart catch. Rahane slowed down after a brisk start and has perished eventually. Rahane c Markande b Unadkat 35(30) [4s-2 6s-1]
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Jadeja, no run, 128.4kph back of a length ball outside off, pace on this time, Jadeja looks to carve it past backward point and misses. It carries to the keeper on the bounce
T Natarajan to Jadeja, 1 run, 117.3kph off-pace bouncer around off, Jadeja waits for it and pulls it to deep mid-wicket
Rahane vs Unadkat in the IPL Runs: 30 Balls: 30 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 10 SR: 100
T Natarajan to Mitchell, 1 run, 134.4kph back of a length ball slanting across Mitchell. He punches it through covers to get off the mark
T Natarajan to Jadeja, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Jadeja drills it towards extra cover but Cummins does well to dive to his right and make a half-stop. Saves certain runs for his side
T Natarajan to Mitchell, 1 run, an off-cutter on a back of a length on leg-stump, Mitchell works it to deep square leg
T Natarajan to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, Jadeja pulls it to deep square leg to retain strike. Only 5 off the over, good restrictive bowling from Natarajan
Unadkat to Jadeja, FOUR, a freebie and Jadeja takes full toll! A full-toss slanting down, Jadeja whips it past the dive of short fine to his right and finds the fence
Unadkat to Jadeja, 1 run, an off-pace back of a length ball wide outside off, Jadeja dabs it towards short third to rotate strike

Unadkat to Mitchell, no run, Unadkat switches to round the wicket and bowls an off-pace length ball at 104kph around off. It grips as it moves away from Mitchell and he mistimes his punch towards Unadkat
Unadkat to Mitchell, 1 run, that back of a length ball took an eternity to arrive to Mitchell. He has to wait for it and he slaps it to deep backward point

Unadkat to Jadeja, no run, another slower bouncer around off, Jadeja shuffles across and mistimes the pull towards short fine. A bit of a yes and no situation between the batters but the shy at the striker's end misses. A direct-hit would have been tight
Unadkat to Jadeja, 1 run, 110.3kph slower shortish ball around off, all Jadeja can do is pull it straight towards deep mid-wicket. 7 off the over
Pat Cummins [3.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Cummins to Jadeja, FOUR, nicely played! 117.2kph back of a length ball wide outside off, Jadeja was expecting it perhaps. He stands tall and slashes it past backward point for a rocketing boundary
Cummins to Jadeja, 2 runs, another slower back of a length ball well outside off, Jadeja chops it through cover-point. The fielder fumbles and that allows the batters
Cummins to Jadeja, 1 run, a full-toss tailing towards the pads, Jadeja looks to flick and gets an inside edge towards the keeper, they sneak in a run
Cummins to Mitchell, 1 run, 139.5kph full ball outside off, Mitchell hits it down to long-on to rotate strike
Cummins to Jadeja, 1 run, the slower balls are the order of the night now. Jadeja reaches out to it and taps it towards deep backward point

Cummins to Mitchell, FOUR, crunched! A slower back of a length ball angling in, Mitchell stands tall and muscles the pull through backward square leg. The fielder in the deep moves to his right but has no chance to cut it off. 150 up for CSK. 13 off the over
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Jadeja, 1 run, a short of length ball slanting across Jadeja. He cuts it towards deep backward point and there's protection there

Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, 2 runs, Mitchell is standing deep inside the crease and Bhuvneshwar nails the yorker around off, Mitchell can only jam it towards long-on. These two are lightning quick between the wickets and they race back for the second. A run-out check upstairs but Mitchell had made his ground with ease
Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, 1 run, an off-pace ball outside off, Mitchell hits it through cover-point

Bhuvneshwar to Jadeja, no run, oh, did Jadeja get in the way of the throw? Klaasen was signaling that he might have got in the way. Was a yorker, Jadeja jammed it out back towards Bhuvneshwar. He threw it back towards the stumps and it seemed like Jadeja was trying to get out of the way rather than getting in the way of the throw. The umpires get together and decide to refer it upstrairs but Cummins has withdrawn the appeal. Good fairplay points there for SRH
Bhuvneshwar to Jadeja, 1 run, full ball outside off, Jadeja hits it through mid-off
Bhuvneshwar to Mitchell, 1 run, a searing yorker on off, Mitchell can only dig it out towards long-on. Brilliant over from Bhuvneshwar
T Natarajan [3.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Mitchell, 1 run, a back of a length ball outside off, sticks on the surface, Mitchell mistimes his flat-batted stroke towards mid-off
T Natarajan to Jadeja, 1 run, 124.7kph off-pace bouncer around off, Jadeja can only pull it towards deep backward square leg
T Natarajan to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Mitchell, out Caught by Abdul Samad!! Mitchell holes out! 134.8kph full ball on middle and off, Mitchell hits it hard but is not able to clear long-on as Samad takes it reverse cup. A big cheer from the crowd as they spot MSD walking in. Mitchell c Abdul Samad b T Natarajan 13(11) [4s-1]
Dhoni draws a big cheer from the crowd, the atmosphere is electrifying. Can he clear the fence?
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Dhoni, no run, 127kph shortish ball on off, lands and grips to cut away from Dhoni. He tries to cut it square of the wicket on the off-side but misses
T Natarajan to Dhoni, 1 run, no fireworks from Dhoni tonight! A slower bouncer slanting across Dhoni. He mistimes the pull over square leg and it goes on the bounce to the fielder

T Natarajan to Jadeja, FOUR, sloppy work! A low full-toss slanting towards the pads, Jadeja flicks it with good timing towards deep backward square leg. Unadkat overruns it a bit and makes a mess of it to concede the boundary. CSK finish with 165/5

21:10 Local Time, 15:40 GMT, 21:10 IST: A good show with the ball from SRH has enabled them to restrict CSK to a slightly below-par total. Mind you, this is a pitch where the slower balls are gripping and as we saw in the second half of the innings, the batters found it really difficult to time their shots. Ravindra fell early trying to play a cross-batted stroke. Gaikwad looked promising but wasted his start. Dube walked in and did his reputation of being a spin basher no harm. Surprisingly, Cummins asked his spinners to bowl two overs to him and that allowed him to get in the flow. Rahane played some eye-catchy strokes but once the ball got a bit older and the SRH pacers used the slower balls, he found it difficult and eventually perished. Cummins sent back the dangerous Dube with a short ball. Two new batters at the crease allowed the hosts to control the show. Mitchell struggled but Jadeja played a decent hand to get CSK to 165. All the SRH pacers were miserly and picked up a wicket each. SRH do have the firepower but CSK also have the arsenal to contain them on a slowish pitch. Would be an interesting run-chase...
CSK innings progression Overs 1-5: 33/1 (RR: 6.6) Overs 6-13: 82/1 (RR: 10.25) Overs 14-20: 50/3 (RR: 7.14)
CSK’s batting today \nLHBs: 88(56) | SR: 157.14 \nRHBs: 75(64) | SR: 117.19
Unadkat in Hyderabad (IPL) Matches: 8 Wickets: 14 Avg: 14.5 SR: 11.1 ER: 7.8 BBI: 5/30

Jaydev Unadkat - To be honest, I don't see much difference in the pitch compared to the last game, but we kept bowling the hard lengths, we varied our pace and bowled with plenty of variations. It was one of those days when the ball went straight to the fielders and there were fewer boundaries conceded. It's about getting the momentum right, if we get runs during the batting PP, we'll go a long way in chasing this score down.

Welcome back for the run-chase! The powerplay will be crucial from the context of both the sides. I reckon SRH would be eyeing to go hard in the first six overs. Meanwhile, the Impact player, Head is all geared up and is raring to walk in with Abhishek Sharma by his side. Natarajan is the one who has been substituted. Meanwhile for CSK, Shivam Dube makes way for Mukesh Choudhary, the Impact sub. Chahar to steam in with the new ball. A slip in place. Here we go...
